[gd_resource type="Theme" load_steps=14 format=3 uid="uid://uy3znkll7jlqy"]

; The one theme for all UI — menus, encounter, loadout, the game shell and its bars all share it, so the
; whole app is one visual system and swapping this resource reskins everything. Debug screens/overlays use
; debug.tres instead. Button looks:
;   Button         — secondary navy card (default)
;   PrimaryButton  — filled teal call-to-action (Play, Resume, Launch)
;   DangerButton   — red-outlined destructive (Quit to Menu)
;   BarButton      — translucent rounded glyph button in the top bars (back, settings, per-stage actions)
; Label looks (colour only; each label keeps its own size as layout):
;   Title / Footnote — menu hero title / faint footnote
;   Heading          — brand-blue readout (round / turn / stats)
;   Caption          — dimmed readout (versus, secondary)
;   ScrapValue       — the scrap counter's count

